# MCP Tools Reference for 1C Development

This file describes available MCP tools for 1C development. Reference this file instead of duplicating tool descriptions.

## 1C Code & Metadata Server (1c-code-metadata-mcp) — 16 tools

Unified server for searching metadata, code, help, forms, XML definitions, XSD validation, and code navigation. Tools are conditionally registered based on `INDEX_*` environment flags.

### Metadata Search

| Tool | Parameters | Purpose | When to Use |
|------|-----------|---------|-------------|
| **metadatasearch** | `query`, `limit=10`, `object_type=""`, `use_grep=false` | Semantic/FTS search in 1C metadata (TXT). `object_type` filters by type (e.g. `Справочник`, `Документ`). `use_grep` forces regex fallback | Search metadata objects, verify existence, find attributes and relationships. Use exact configuration names (e.g. `'Справочники.Контрагенты.Реквизиты'`) |
| **get_metadata_details** | `object_name` | Full metadata structure: attributes with types, tabular parts, synonyms, properties | Get complete object structure when you already know the name (e.g. `'Номенклатура'`, `'Документ.РеализацияТоваровУслуг'`) |

### Code Search & Navigation

| Tool | Parameters | Purpose | When to Use |
|------|-----------|---------|-------------|
| **codesearch** | `query`, `limit=5`, `use_grep=false` | Hybrid search in BSL modules, forms, and common modules | Find code patterns, check usages, verify implementations. `query` can be code, function name, or comment |
| **search_function** | `name`, `exact=true`, `limit=10` | Find BSL procedures/functions by name via structural FTS index. `exact=true` does case-insensitive match with auto-fallback to fuzzy | Find specific procedure/function definition (e.g. `'ОбработкаПроведения'`, `'ПриСозданииНаСервере'`) |
| **get_module_structure** | `module_path` | Full module structure: all procedures, functions, regions, and statistics | Understand module before editing. Get overview of what a module contains |
| **get_method_call_hierarchy** | `method_name`, `direction="both"`, `depth=3` | Call graph: who calls this method (`callers`), what it calls (`callees`), or `both` | Understand call chains, impact analysis, find hot paths |
| **graph_dependencies** | `object_name`, `direction="both"`, `limit=50` | Dependency graph: `forward` (what this uses), `reverse` (who uses this), or `both` | Impact analysis before refactoring, understand object relationships |
| **bsl_scope_members** | `context`, `member_type="all"` | Available methods, properties, events for a BSL context string. `member_type`: `all`, `methods`, `properties`, `events` | Discover available API for an object (e.g. `'Справочник.Номенклатура'`, `'Глобальный'`) |

### Help Search

| Tool | Parameters | Purpose | When to Use |
|------|-----------|---------|-------------|
| **helpsearch** | `query`, `limit=5`, `use_grep=false` | Search HTML help and user documentation | Find help topics, understand metadata object purpose, find functional descriptions |

### Metadata XML & Forms

| Tool | Parameters | Purpose | When to Use |
|------|-----------|---------|-------------|
| **search_metadata_xml** | `query`, `limit=10` | Semantic search over all metadata XML definitions (attributes, types, tabular parts, dimensions, resources) | Find configuration objects by meaning/description for XML generation examples (e.g. `'документы для учёта оплат'`, `'регистр остатков товаров'`) |
| **search_metadata_forms** | `query`, `limit=10` | Search forms by metadata object name, form name, or title | Find existing forms as examples before generating new ones (e.g. `'Номенклатура'`, `'ФормаЭлемента'`) |
| **get_metadata_form_details** | `object_name`, `form_name=""` | Full form structure: element hierarchy with types and data bindings, form attributes, commands, event handlers | Study form layout before modification or as a reference for generating a new form |

### XSD Schemas & Validation

| Tool | Parameters | Purpose | When to Use |
|------|-----------|---------|-------------|
| **get_xsd_schema** | `object_type` | Generated XSD for a metadata type (`Справочник`, `Документ`, `РегистрСведений`, `РегистрНакопления`, `Роль`) or sub-object type (`Форма`, `СКД`, `Макет`). English aliases accepted | Get XML structure rules before generating/modifying metadata XML |
| **verify_xml** | `xml_content`, `object_type` | Validate XML string against XSD. Returns `status` (`valid`/`invalid`/`error`/`not_found`) and `errors` list | Validate generated or modified XML before committing |

### Administration

| Tool | Parameters | Purpose | When to Use |
|------|-----------|---------|-------------|
| **reindex** | `force=false` | Trigger background reindexation. `force=true` wipes and rebuilds all indexes from scratch | After configuration changes, when search results seem stale |
| **stats** | *(none)* | Index statistics: document counts per collection, embedding provider, last indexation time, reindex schedule | Diagnostics, verify indexing status |

## Documentation Search (1C-docs-mcp)

| Tool | Purpose | When to Use |
|------|---------|-------------|
| **docsearch** | Search 1C platform documentation by description (hybrid: vector + BM25) | Search for built-in functions by description, find platform features when exact name is unknown |
| **docinfo** | Look up 1C platform documentation by exact object/method name | Get documentation for a known object or method (e.g., `"ТаблицаЗначений"`, `"Массив.Найти"`, `"Запрос"`) |

> **Prefer docinfo for known names** — use `docinfo` for precise lookup by exact name; use `docsearch` for fuzzy/semantic search when the exact name is unknown.

## Code Templates & Memory (1c-templates-mcp)

| Tool | Purpose | When to Use |
|------|---------|-------------|
| **templatesearch** | Search code templates and examples (semantic + fulltext, 2000+ templates) | Find architectural patterns, implementation examples before writing code |
| **ssl_search** | Search SSL (БСП) functions | Find standard library functions to reuse |

## Graph Metadata (1c-graph-metadata-mcp)

| Tool | Purpose | When to Use |
|------|---------|-------------|
| **search_metadata** | Search metadata via graph database (Cypher-based) | Alternative to `metadatasearch` when graph queries are needed |
| **get_metadata_prompt** | Get instructions for generating a Cypher query | When `search_metadata` / `metadatasearch` are unavailable or graph traversal is needed |
| **execute_metadata_cypher** | Execute metadata Cypher query | After `get_metadata_prompt` |
| **business_search** | Semantic search for metadata by natural language | Find objects by business description when you don't know the technical name |
| **answer_metadata_question** | Get answers about how metadata objects work | Understand metadata behavior and purpose |

> **metadatasearch vs search_metadata**: `metadatasearch` (1c-code-metadata-mcp) uses vector/FTS search over exported TXT files. `search_metadata` (1c-graph-metadata-mcp) uses a Cypher graph database. Both find metadata objects; prefer `metadatasearch` + `get_metadata_details` for structural queries about attributes and types.

## Code Quality (1c-syntax-checker-mcp)

| Tool | Purpose | When to Use |
|------|---------|-------------|
| **syntaxcheck** | Check BSL syntax and style via BSL Language Server | After writing code, verify no errors. **Limit: 3 times per cycle** |

## 1CCodeChecker Tools (1С:Напарник, 1c-code-check-mcp)

**11 tools** for code analysis, review, modification, and documentation access.

### Code Analysis & Modification

| Tool | Purpose | When to Use |
|------|---------|-------------|
| **check_1c_code** | Technical check: syntax, logic, performance | After writing code — find bugs and performance issues |
| **review_1c_code** | Code review: style, ITS standards, naming, structure | After writing code — ensure standards compliance |
| **rewrite_1c_code** | AI rewrites code with improvements (optional `goal`: `optimize`, `readability`, `error handling`) | When code needs significant improvement |
| **modify_1c_code** | Modify or generate code by explicit instruction | Apply targeted changes, fix specific bugs, add features |
| **ask_1c_ai** | Free-form question to 1С:Напарник (preserves dialog context) | Architecture questions, concept explanations, advice |

### Documentation & Knowledge Base

| Tool | Purpose | When to Use |
|------|---------|-------------|
| **search_1c_documentation** | Search platform docs for specific version (e.g. `v8.3.25`) | Version-specific method signatures, platform features |
| **onec_help** | Search platform docs (latest version) | Quick lookup of platform features, methods, types |
| **its_help** | Search ITS knowledge base (standards, methodologies) | Find ITS standards, best practices. **Returns document IDs → use `fetch_its`** |
| **fetch_its** | Read full ITS document by ID | **Always use after `its_help`** to read found articles. Special IDs: `root`, `v8std` |
| **diff_1c_documentation_versions** | Compare docs between platform versions | Check changes between versions (e.g. `v8.3.25` → `v8.5.1`) |
| **config_help** | Search docs for specific configs (ERP, БП, ЗУП, УТ) | Config-specific business logic, object descriptions |

> **Key workflow**: `its_help` → get document IDs → `fetch_its` with each ID to read full content. Never ignore ITS article references.

## Tool Usage by Task

### Writing New Code
1. **templatesearch** — find similar implementations
2. **codesearch** — check existing patterns in configuration
3. **search_function** — find existing procedures/functions by name to reuse
4. **get_module_structure** — understand the module you're about to edit
5. **metadatasearch** / **get_metadata_details** — verify metadata structure and attribute types
6. **bsl_scope_members** — discover available methods/properties for the context you're working with
7. **docinfo** — verify built-in functions/methods by exact name; **docsearch** — search by description
8. **ssl_search** — find reusable SSL functions
9. **syntaxcheck** — verify syntax after writing
10. **check_1c_code** — find logic and performance issues
11. **review_1c_code** — verify style and standards compliance

### Code Review
1. **codesearch** — verify pattern compliance
2. **graph_dependencies** — analyze impact of the code being reviewed
3. **get_method_call_hierarchy** — trace call chains, find affected callers
4. **metadatasearch** / **get_metadata_details** — check correct metadata usage
5. **docinfo** — verify method/property existence by exact name; **docsearch** — search by description
6. **review_1c_code** — check style and ITS standards compliance
7. **check_1c_code** — find bugs and performance issues
8. **its_help** → **fetch_its** — verify against ITS standards

### Architecture Design
1. **metadatasearch** / **get_metadata_details** — understand existing metadata structure
2. **graph_dependencies** — map relationships between configuration objects
3. **codesearch** — find existing patterns
4. **get_method_call_hierarchy** — understand code coupling
5. **templatesearch** — find architectural templates
6. **ask_1c_ai** — get architectural advice from 1С:Напарник
7. **config_help** — understand how specific configurations implement patterns

### Error Fixing
1. **syntaxcheck** — identify syntax errors
2. **check_1c_code** — identify logic and performance problems
3. **search_function** — find the problematic procedure/function
4. **get_module_structure** — understand module context around the error
5. **get_method_call_hierarchy** — trace how the error propagates
6. **docinfo** — verify correct function/method names; **docsearch** — search if unsure
7. **metadatasearch** / **get_metadata_details** — verify metadata object names and attributes
8. **codesearch** — find correct usage patterns
9. **modify_1c_code** — apply targeted fixes via AI

### Performance Optimization
1. **codesearch** — find slow patterns
2. **get_method_call_hierarchy** — identify hot call paths
3. **graph_dependencies** — find objects causing cascading performance issues
4. **metadatasearch** / **get_metadata_details** — check indexes and metadata structure
5. **check_1c_code** — analyze performance issues
6. **rewrite_1c_code** — get AI-optimized code (with `goal: optimize`)
7. **templatesearch** — find optimized patterns
8. **its_help** → **fetch_its** — find ITS performance standards

### Generating/Modifying Metadata XML
1. **search_metadata_xml** — find similar XML definitions as examples
2. **get_xsd_schema** — get XSD schema for the target metadata type to know expected structure
3. Write/modify XML according to schema and examples
4. **verify_xml** — validate generated XML against XSD; fix errors if any
5. Use **1c-metadata-manage** skill to compile and deploy

### Form Analysis and Generation
1. **search_metadata_forms** — find similar existing forms in the configuration
2. **get_metadata_form_details** — study the structure of a found similar form (elements, bindings, commands, events)
3. **search_metadata_xml** — find XML examples for the target metadata type
4. **get_xsd_schema**(`"Форма"`) — get XSD schema for form XML structure
5. Generate Form.xml based on examples and schema
6. **verify_xml** — validate the generated Form.xml against XSD
7. Use **1c-metadata-manage** skill (form-manage section) to compile and validate

### Documentation
1. **codesearch** — find code to document
2. **metadatasearch** / **get_metadata_details** — understand metadata structure
3. **get_module_structure** — get procedure/function list for documentation
4. **docinfo** — get documentation for a specific object/method; **docsearch** — search by description
5. **helpsearch** — find existing help articles
6. **its_help** → **fetch_its** — find and read ITS methodological articles
7. **search_1c_documentation** — find version-specific platform docs

### Comparing Platform Versions
1. **diff_1c_documentation_versions** — see what changed between versions
2. **search_1c_documentation** — search docs for specific version

## Important Rules

1. **Always search before writing** — use `templatesearch` and `codesearch` first
2. **Verify against documentation** — use `docinfo` for known names, `docsearch` for description-based search
3. **Check metadata exists** — use `metadatasearch` + `get_metadata_details` before using objects
4. **Use structural tools** — `search_function`, `get_module_structure`, `get_method_call_hierarchy` for code navigation instead of manual grep
5. **Validate generated XML** — always use `get_xsd_schema` before writing XML and `verify_xml` after
6. **Limit syntaxcheck** — maximum 3 times per cycle, then move on
7. **Don't use Grep** — when MCP tools are available for code search
8. **Always follow up `its_help` with `fetch_its`** — read full ITS article content by ID
9. **Use 1CCodeChecker tools actively** — `check_1c_code` and `review_1c_code` after every code change
10. **Use `graph_dependencies`** — before refactoring to understand impact
